sses, vaccination policies, and community spotlights. Sunset Kennels partners with nearby shelters, trainers, and pet-forward cafes to keep Lodi's vibrant dog scene moving together.49:T5f9,Sycamore Lane Kennels anchors Lodi's dog-loving rhythm as a dog park that marries expansive play yards with concierge-level care. Located in Lodi, CA, the park is tucked near 5111 W Sargent Rd, Lodi, CA 95242 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.8-star average across 253 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Drop-in passes, punch cards, and community days keep the experience accessible without sacrificing premium touches.\n\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. Sycamore Lane Kennels curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Lodi's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at Sycamore Lane Kennels, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check http://www.sycamorelanekennels.com/index.php for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights.4a:T5f4,Vinewood Park anchors Lodi's dog-loving rhythm as a dog park that marries expansive play yards with concierge-level care. Located in Lodi, CA, the park is tucked near 931 Virginia Ave, Lodi, CA 95242 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.5-star average across 230 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Drop-in passes, punch cards, and community days keep the experience accessible without sacrificing premium touches.\n\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. Vinewood Park curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Lodi's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at Vinewood Park, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check https://www.lodi.gov/Facilities/Facility/Details/Vinewood-Park-3 for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights.35:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"className\":\"city-insights-section\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L45\",null,{\"parks\":[{\"id\":\"ChIJ58edBhinmoARGuwQr77Kdak\",\"name\":\"All Dogs Sports Park, LLC\",\"businessType\":\"Dog Park\",\"description\":\"$46\",\"slug\":\"all-dogs-sports-park-llc\",\"address\":\"5111 W Sargent Rd\",\"street\":\"5111 W Sargent Rd\",\"city\":\"Lodi\",\"state\":\"CA\",\"zipCode\":\"95242\",\"full_address\":\"5111 W Sargent Rd, Lodi, CA 95242\",\"latitude\":38.1327813,\"longitude\":-121.3764529,\"googlePlaceId\":\"ChIJ58edBhinmoARGuwQr77Kdak\",\"phone\":\"(209) 334-1316\",\"website\":\"http://www.alldogssportspark.com/\",\"photos\":